test failed whenever that port was already in use. I changed [KafkaClientsTest.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2969-b4447c57/tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/KafkaClientsTest.java:84) to allocate a free local port at startup and reuse that address for the broker, admin client, producer, and consumer.\\n\\nVerification passed with:\\n```bash\\nGRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/gdrive/bin/graalvm-jdk-25.0.3+9.1 \\\\\\nGVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=current-defaults \\\\\\nJAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/gdrive/bin/graalvm-jdk-25.0.3+9.1 \\\\\\n./gradlew testInfra -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:3.5.2 -Pparallelism=1 --stacktrace\\n```\\n\\nResult: `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `All commands succeeded for coordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:3.5.2.`\\n\\nThe worktree also contains unrelated pre-existing modified `stats/.../stats.json` files; I left those untouched.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_15\",\"type\":\"todo_list\",\"items\":[{\"text\":\"Inspect failing testInfra logs and isolate root cause\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Patch kafka-clients test to avoid fixed broker port collision\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Re-run targeted testInfra verification\",\"completed\":true}]}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1152762,\"cached_input_tokens\":1102720,\"output_tokens\":9667,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":2886}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
