{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed to produce a PR-ready update for `org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-mapreduce-client-app:2.7.3`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2969-library-new-request-org.apache.hadoop-hadoop-mapreduce-client-app-2.7.3-c04c67df\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation quality gate around dynamic-access coverage, not metadata validation or the final local CI reruns. The final artifacts show `0/6` dynamic-access coverage in `stats/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-mapreduce-client-app/2.7.3/stats.json`, and `stats/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-mapreduce-client-app/2.7.3/execution-metrics.json` records `status: success`, `iterations: 4`, `generated_loc: 330`, `metadata_entries: 12`, and only `2.6%` code coverage. The generated `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-mapreduce-client-app/2.7.3/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop/hadoop_mapreduce_client_app/Hadoop_mapreduce_client_appTest.java` passes under native image in the later reruns, but it still did not cover any of the six tracked reflective calls.\n\nThere was an earlier real native-image failure during generation: `forge/logs/org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-mapreduce-client-app:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-09T05-39-52-194977Z.log` shows `:nativeTest` failing with `ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.hadoop.yarn.factories.impl.pb.RecordFactoryPBImpl` and follow-on `NoClassDefFoundError` failures from `org.apache.hadoop.yarn.util.Records`. That appears fixed in the preserved work: `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-09T07-16-51-067322Z.log`, `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-09T07-18-09-572812Z.log`, and `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-09T07-19-13-290554Z.log` all pass, and `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-09T07-16-52-185413Z.log`, `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-09T07-18-10-766375Z.log`, and `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-09T07-19-14-395046Z.log` all show the `native-image run` stage succeeding.\n\nRecommended manual follow-up:\n- Review the preserved branch and either salvage or replace the generated test so it exercises the reflective YARN PB record-factory path implicated by the initial `RecordFactoryPBImpl` failure.\n- Recompute the targeted dynamic-access report/stats for `org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-mapreduce-client-app:2.7.3` and confirm coverage moves above `0/6`.\n- If the tests do hit that path but coverage still stays at `0/6`, inspect the dynamic-access report generation for this coordinate before opening a PR."}}
